{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Even as the emphasis shifts to the keyboard, experts say that learning to write by hand improves motor skills, memory and creativity.", "abstract": "Common Core standards in education, which have been accepted in most states, place little emphasis on handwriting after the first grade, but research shows that process of writing by hand is important to a number of cognitive processes, and not just legibility; evidence suggests that learning to write by hand helps children better generate ideas and retain information.", "section_name": "Science", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Maria", "role": "reported", "lastname": "KONNIKOVA", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MARIA KONNIKOVA", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/03/science/whats-lost-as-handwriting-fades.html", "lead_paragraph": "Even as the emphasis shifts to the keyboard, experts say that learning to write by hand improves motor skills, memory and creativity.", "headline": {"main": "What\u2019s Lost as Handwriting Fades", "print_headline": "What\u2019s Lost as Handwriting Fades"}, "_id": "538cc62e38f0d8757fa21a7f", "word_count": "1062", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/06/03/science/03JPWRIT1/03JPWRIT1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/06/03/science/03JPWRIT1/03JPWRIT1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 395, "url": "images/2014/06/03/science/03JPWRIT1/03JPWRIT1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/06/03/science/03JPWRIT1/03JPWRIT1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "395"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/06/03/science/03WRIT/03WRIT-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/06/03/science/03WRIT/03WRIT-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": "75", "thumbnailheight